Prerequisites:

No hardcording files names

For generating certificates, we use KeyTool

Java documentation that can be used:
    1. Java Crypto Documentation: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/security/crypto/CryptoSpec.html
    2. Java Crypto Name Standards (mandatory): https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/security/StandardNames.html
    3. Bouncy Castle Documentation: https://www.bouncycastle.org/specifications.html

The second documentation is essential, due to having to memorize algorithms instead.

Schedule 19th and 20th of October 2024:
    1. Course 1.1 schedule:
        1. Java Recap
        2. Number Types &  different representations (hex, binary)
        3. String Class (comparing strings)
        4. How to get HEX String representation for Byte Arrays (Char on 2 bytes)
        5. Char vs Byte
        6. Bitwise operations -> shifting, |, &, ^
        7. Bit masks
        8. Collections (Lists, Sets, Maps)
        9. Files (Text Files & Binary Files) & File System

    2. Course 1.2 (+ Course 2.1 & 2.2)schedule:
        1. JCA:
            1. Message Digest (MD5)
            2. MAC & HMAC
            3. PBKDF
            4. Symmetric Encryption (Block Ciphers - modes: ECB & CBC & CTR)
            5. Symmetric Stream Cypher - OTP
            5. TRNG vs PRNG & generating random keys
            6. Asymmetric Encryption (LSA & ECC)
            7. Digital Signature
